<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC) SYSTEM - ProStar - REMOVE AND INSTALL - A/C COMPRESSOR/CLUTCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl160390804" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>A/C COMPRESSOR/CLUTCH</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Depending on the vehicle model/engine combination, replacement of certain components may require the
                removal of nearby assemblies to gain access to compressor mounting bolts and A/C lines. Refer to the
                appropriate section(s) in the Master Service Manual for additional procedures.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1603926">Figure 26</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following Remove and Install procedures.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discharge A/C system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16039_HL160390905.xml" xrefid="hl160390905">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl160390905"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove or loosen compressor belt.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect compressor clutch wiring connector (4, Figure 26) from engine wire harness.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect both refrigerant line fittings at compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When removing mounting bolts from side mounted compressors, support compressor to prevent
                        possible damage to mounting bolts and/or compressor.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four compressor mounting bolts (5), noting location and orientation of any
                    brackets secured by mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove compressor assembly (1) from engine.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603926" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g1603926.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. A/C Compressor (Typical Installation)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. A/C COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DISCHARGE PORT/LINE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SUCTION PORT/LINE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MOUNTING BOLT (QTY 4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Verify that the clutch is installed on the compressor before performing the following
                        installation procedure.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If system is to be flushed or purged, perform that operation before reassembling system.
                    Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16039_HL160390909.xml" xrefid="hl160390909">PURGING OR FLUSHING THE AIR
                        CONDITIONING SYSTEM
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl160390909"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Before installing compressor, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16039_HL160390910.xml" xrefid="hl160390910">OIL FILL GUIDELINES</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl160390910"/>. The oil shipped in new compressors must be drained when determining the
                    correct amount of refrigerant oil to be added to the system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install compressor assembly including any brackets previously secured by the compressor
                    mounting bolts. Tighten to 23 to 29 N.m (16.9 to 21.4 lbf-ft).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Always lubricate O-rings with mineral-based oil during installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using new O-rings and C-plates connect refrigerant line fittings at compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect compressor clutch wiring connector to engine harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and align compressor belt.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Recharge A/C system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16039_HL160390907.xml" xrefid="hl160390907">CHARGING THE AIR CONDITIONING
                        SYSTEM
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl160390907"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install any assemblies that were removed to gain access to the compressor.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
